# Copy this file to .env and fill in real values for anything you want to
# actually connect. BisaAI and checkout both have honest mock fallbacks
# and run without any secrets below — Auth is the one exception: the
# Supabase values are required for sign-up/login/Google sign-in to work
# at all, there's no mock auth left to fall back to.

# --- Database ---
# SQLite for local dev. Swapping to hosted Postgres later (Neon/Supabase)
# is just changing this URL + the `provider` line in prisma/schema.prisma.
DATABASE_URL="file:./dev.db"

# --- Auth (Supabase) ---
# Real authentication — email/password + Google OAuth — via Supabase Auth.
# This app's own data (WeddingPlan, Guest, BudgetCategory, ...) still
# lives in the local SQLite database above; Supabase is the identity
# provider only. src/lib/session.ts links the two via User.supabaseId.
# NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL / NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY: from your
# Supabase project's Settings -> API page — safe to expose to the browser.
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=""
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=""
# SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY: same page, the *secret* service_role key.
# Server-only, never exposed to the browser — never give this (or any
# variable like it) a NEXT_PUBLIC_ prefix. Used by prisma/seed.ts (to
# create the seeded demo account's real Supabase identity via the Admin
# API) and by scripts/setup-test-users.ts (see below). Leave blank to
# skip those Admin API steps; the rest of the seed still runs.
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=""

# Production email delivery: Supabase's own default email sending is
# rate-limited and meant for development only — for a real deployment,
# configure a custom SMTP provider (Resend, Postmark, SES, ...) directly
# in the Supabase dashboard under Authentication -> Settings -> SMTP
# Settings. This is a Supabase project setting, not an env var this app
# reads itself — nothing to add here, since GoTrue (Supabase's auth
# server) sends the email, not this codebase. If your SMTP provider ever
# needs a key entered *here* instead (it shouldn't, for this project),
# add it as a server-only variable and never prefix it NEXT_PUBLIC_.

# --- Test accounts (local/dev only) ---
# Used exclusively by `npm run setup:test-users`
# (scripts/setup-test-users.ts) to create or repair the two seeded test
# accounts (free@test.com on the Free plan, and the dev-only Wedding Pass
# account exported as TEST_PASS_USER_EMAIL from src/lib/session.ts) when
# you've forgotten their passwords. Leave blank in any environment this
# script shouldn't run in — it refuses to run at all if either is unset.
# Never commit real values; this file only ever ships blank placeholders.
TEST_FREE_USER_PASSWORD=""
TEST_PAID_USER_PASSWORD=""

# --- BisaAI provider ---
# "mock" (default) uses the labelled mock implementations in src/lib/bisaai.ts.
# Set to "openai" or "anthropic" once real-integration TODOs are implemented.
BISAAI_PROVIDER="mock"
OPENAI_API_KEY=""
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=""

# --- Payments (Paystack: card + Ghana Mobile Money) ---
# Leave blank for local dev — checkout falls back to an honest demo stub
# (see lib/payments/paystack.ts's isPaystackConfigured() and
# checkout/page.tsx) when this isn't set. Set a real Paystack **test**
# secret key here to exercise the real flow: src/lib/payments/paystack.ts
# calls the API, server/actions/billing.ts's startPayment() creates the
# Payment row and redirects to Paystack, and
# src/app/api/webhooks/paystack/route.ts is what actually grants the
# Wedding Pass once Paystack confirms the charge (configure this route's
# full URL as the webhook endpoint in the Paystack dashboard). Card and
# mobile money (MTN MoMo, Telecel, AT) are both handled by Paystack
# automatically for a GHS transaction — no separate Hubtel integration.
PAYSTACK_SECRET_KEY=""

# --- App ---
# The app's own canonical origin — this project's equivalent of a
# "site URL" env var. Used to build absolute redirect URLs for Supabase
# auth emails (signup confirmation, password reset — see lib/site-url.ts)
# so they always point at the right environment instead of whatever
# Supabase's dashboard "Site URL" happens to be set to. Set this to your
# real Vercel production URL in Vercel's own env var settings (e.g.
# "https://your-app.vercel.app"); leave the localhost default for local dev.
NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL="http://localhost:3000"
